%% Sequence Diagram — Inference Request with Fallback (decomposed subsystems)
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client (SDK)
    participant I as router-ingress
    participant Sec as router-security
    participant PE as Policy Engine
    participant Cache as router-cache (Redis)
    participant EP as Execution Planner
    participant ER as Execution Runtime
    participant P1 as provider-anthropic
    participant P2 as provider-openai
    participant K as Kafka

    C->>I: POST /v1/inference (policy, messages)
    I->>Sec: authenticate + authorize + rate-limit check
    Sec-->>I: OK (tenantId resolved)
    I->>PE: resolve policy for tenant + request overrides

    PE->>PE: merge system → tenant → request policy
    PE-->>I: effective RoutingPolicy

    I->>Cache: lookup(cacheKey)
    Cache-->>I: miss

    I->>EP: plan(RoutingPolicy, providers)
    EP->>EP: enumerate eligible candidates (capability, privacy tier)
    EP->>Cache: fetch live provider scores
    Cache-->>EP: scores (latency, error rate, cost, capacity)
    EP->>EP: RoutingStrategy.rank() → [anthropic, openai]
    EP-->>I: ranked candidate list

    I->>ER: execute(rankedCandidates, request)
    ER->>P1: invoke(request)  %% attempt 1
    P1-->>ER: 503 Service Unavailable

    Note over ER: retryable failure, pre-first-byte → advance to next candidate

    ER->>P2: invoke(request)  %% attempt 2
    P2-->>ER: 200 OK (completion)

    ER->>ER: normalize response
    ER-->>I: InferenceResponse (routing trace: anthropic failed, openai succeeded)
    I-->>C: 200 OK

    ER-)K: emit usage/cost/latency event (async, off hot path)
    K-)Cache: async score update consumer refreshes provider scores
